      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented user qualification process and independent simulation review must be in place to detect analyst-introduced errors in boundary conditions, material properties, and post-processing.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of boundary condition inputs or post-processing scripts was performed. User qualification records are absent. Achieved level 1 is two steps below required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis model form must be justified through systematic comparison of competing model forms against experimental data with sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness of the selected form.",
      "rationale": "A single power-law hemolysis model is used without comparison to alternative model forms such as the Giersiepen-Wurzinger or Taskin models. No model-form sensitivity analysis is documented. Achieved level 1 is four steps below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
